  "prompt": "What did George Lucas think of the Force Awakens?",
  "response": "George Lucas has shared mixed feelings about \"Star Wars: The Force Awakens.\" While he acknowledged the film's commercial success and appreciated its ability to engage a new generation of fans, he also expressed disappointment regarding the creative direction it took. Lucas had originally envisioned a different storyline and thematic focus for the sequel trilogy, and he felt that the film did not align with his vision for the franchise. He mentioned that he felt the film relied heavily on nostalgia and the original trilogy elements rather than exploring new concepts. Overall, while he recognized the positive aspects of \"The Force Awakens,\" his comments indicated a sense of separation from the project's direction.",
